text: Finally found the best laksa in town!! Portion is big enough and value for money. Their goreng Pisang is the bomb! Friendly staff! Must come here and give a try ðŸ˜œ

Passed by this shop and this jemput jemput pisang (fried banana balls) caught my attention. It's not perfectly round. But the taste is definitely 100% homemade n delicious. I can taste the banana. Unlike other shops, where the kuih is mostly flour.

Located along Arab Street, opposite Golden Landmark. Delightful Laksa Ikan Kembong with a rich and solid soup at this spot. Pair it with the flavorful Otah Otah and a satisfying Teh Tarikâ€”all at an attractive price. Don't miss their delectable curry puffs and fried bananas! Highly recommended, but limited seating, so consider a takeaway for a treat on the go.

Curry puffs and their other snacks are made fresh and eating them while its hot makes a huge difference. Price is very reasonable and they justify by the size of their snacks. Staffs are prompt and courteous with their service. I have bumped into Mediacorp celebrity who was patronizing this store. He did mention the laksa is a delicious dish.  Die Die Must Try .
Pondok.Makan serves the best laksa, kueh-mueh and iced tea in Singapore. Their service has always been great since day 1. Price of the food are affordable. Sure to have your tummy happy!
